                    <history>
                        <origin>
                            <p>
                                <origPlace>
                                    <placeName cert="low" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100081">Sweden</placeName>
                                </origPlace>, <origDate notAfter="1500" notBefore="1451">15th century, second half</origDate>.</p>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>Early provenance unknown. On account of the saints in the litany, a former librarian suggests that it was produced for use in Västerås diocese, but this seems uncertain since both St Botvid and St Katarina of Vadstena are listed in the litany, both of whom are not in the Västerås calendar.</p>
                        </provenance>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>According to a note on <locus from="LCI" to="LCI" scheme="other"/> it belonged to the library of <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/101246">Johan Lüdeke</persName> (1772-1838). </p>
                        </provenance>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>According to a note on LCI it belonged to <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102782">Peter von Möller</persName> (1809-1883).</p>
                        </provenance>
                        <acquisition>
                            <p>Donated to the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100004">National Library</orgName> by <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102782">Peter von Möller</persName>, as evidenced by a note on <locus from="LCI" to="LCI" scheme="other"/>.</p>
                        </acquisition>
                    </history>
